Samsung has launched its latest PC monitor, the C34J791 (the CJ79 for short). The display is a 34-inch 1,500R curved QLED screen which supports Thunderbolt 3 connectivity – via two ports. The Samsung monitor packs a 3,440×1,440 resolution across a 21:9 aspect ratio, and allows for picture-by-picture functionality. Other specifications include a 4ms response time, 100Hz refresh rate, a 3,000:1 contrast ratio, support for AMD FreeSync, built-in speakers, and VA panel technology. Samsung said the CJ79 will be available in Europe first, and will be available worldwide soon. No international pricing was supplied. 